---
title: One-Pot Vegan Cauliflower & Bean Soup with Cilantro & Blue Corn Tortilla Chips
description: This hearty, flavorful vegan soup is ready in under 30 minutes and cooks in one pot, making cleanup a breeze! Cauliflower and beans are simmered in a richly-spiced broth—veggie stock, onion, green pepper, tomatoes, and Southwest seasonings—until tender. Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve crunchy blue corn tortilla chips alongside for a SOUP-er supper.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pot-vegan-cauliflower-bean-soup-f909b58a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pot-vegan-cauliflower-bean-soup-630e489862e1d857fa01c11b-2c909e8d.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-vegan-cauliflower-bean-soup-630e489862e1d857fa01c11b
cuisine: Mexican
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 510 kcal
  fat: 15 g
  saturated fat: 2 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 16 g
  sodium: 2530 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Core, deseed, and finely dice @long green pepper{1}. Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} (large pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of oil. Stir in @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, tomato, and @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}; cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir @black beans{1%418g can} and their liquid, cauliflower, @Tex-Mex paste{1}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and 1 1/2 cups water (2 1/2 cups for 4 servings) into #pot{} with veggies.

Bring to a simmer, then cover and reduce heat to medium low. Cook until cauliflower is tender and soup has thickened slightly, ~{7-10%minutes}.

> If soup isn't thick enough, cook until it reaches desired consistency. If soup seems too thick, add a splash more water.

Taste and season with @salt{1.5%tsp} (2 1/2 tsp for 4 servings) and @pepper{}.

Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(leaves picked from stems).

Divide soup between bowls and sprinkle with cilantro. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} on the side.